Description: Construct and decorate a finny friend to take home as a souvenir.
Group: G. H. Cook Biochemistry & Microbiology Club

Title: Instamatic Photobooth
Description: Enjoy instant portrait photography and view the student works on display.

Title: Big Dig
Description: Search our mock archaeological dig, and learn how excavation works and how to interpret findings.

Title: Fossils & Human Evolution
Description: Examine casts of important fossils. Talk with experts about what these casts might say about human evolution.

Title: Name That Primate!
Description: Explore the primate branch of your family tree. Match the calls of primates with their photos.

Title: Arrowheads and Stone Tools
Description: Handle artifacts as old as 1.5 million years!

Title: Language Diversity Challenge
Description: Learn how our views of language can shape both connections and divides.

Title: Find the Palm Oil
Description: Pick the product that poses a grave threat to primates all over the world.

Title: 3rd Annual Let's Do Lunch with the Executive Dean
Description: Meet classmates, friends, faculty, students--and the dean! Enjoy barbecue, gifts, and fun.
Group: Office of the Executive Dean, School of Environmental and Biological Sciences

Title: Nutritional Sciences Graduate Student Organization
Description: Make your own granola or trail mix and play fun nutrition-education games.

Title: Luso-American Portuguese Club
Description: Experience the many cultures of Portuguese-speaking countries.
Group: Luso American Club, Portuguese Language Club

Title: Dig It!
Description: Go "underground" in our soil tunnel. Learn about soil and plant diagnostic services at Rutgers. Plant giveaways, too!
Group: Department of Plant Biology and Pathology

Title: Slow Food Rutgers
Description: Taste fresh, local foods. Connect with local food sources and local foodie communities that respect healthy eating and healthy people.

Title: RUDASA Trivia Challenge
Description: Test your knowledge about designing equal-access activities. Learn "I want candy" and other phrases in American Sign Language.

Title: Douglass Residential College: History Detectives
Description: Discover the history of Rutgers' residential college for women through trivia games and more.

Title: Know Your Primates!
Description: Learn how primates are endangered by deforestation, climate change, and other human activities.

Title: Do You Know Africa?
Description: Choose a question on a cutout board of Africa to win a prize.

Title: Fight the Knight
Description: Put on a pair of boxing gloves and fight the Black Knight.

Title: Focus on Fossil Fuels
Description: Discuss fossil fuel issues with club members, including climate change and the role of the oil and gas industry.

Title: Meet Delta Upsilon
Description: Talk with members about our volunteer work, including building schools in Jamaica.

Title: Make a Rockin' Friend!
Description: Create a gneiss little pet rock to take home, and see what else the club has to offer.

Title: Queens Chorale Music Trivia
Description: Answer trivia questions about choral and classical music and learn solfege hand signs.

Title: Meet the Mounted Patrol
Description: Tour the barn, admire the horses, and speak with the student members of Rutgers' mounted patrol.

Title: AJES Cosplay Prop Photo-Op
Description: Channel your favorite character with props and costumes. Yummy baked goods, too!

Title: Skateboarding and Longboarding Lessons
Description: Ollie, fakie, pop shuv-it? See demonstrations by club members.

Title: Color Waves
Description: Tie-dye shirts and learn about the color spectrum, light waves, and color perception. Science and fun combined!

Title: From Scrap to Seating: Landscape Upcycle
Description: Be impressed by students' creative thinking as they reuse different materials in the landscape.
Group: American Society of Landscape Architecture, Rutgers Student Chapter

Title: Design a Rutgers Mortarboard
Description: What year will you graduate from Rutgers? Design a graduation cap that tells the world.
Group: Douglass Orientation Committee, Office of First Year Experiences

Title: New Jersey Veterans Helpline
Description: Learn about a 24/7 helpline for veterans and their family members.

Title: Cabaret Theatre's Theater Games
Description: Have fun with family-friendly theater games led by troupe members.

Title: Scarlet Cross
Description: Mingle with members and learn about medieval food, dance, combat, costume, and more.

Title: (2:30 p.m.) The World's Largest Egg Toss
Description: Anyone from 5 - 105 years of age can join in on the World's Largest Egg Toss.  Grab a partner and bring your spirit.  Do you have what it takes or will the yolk be on you?

Title: (1 p.m.) Take me out to the Ball Game... Let's root for R Home Team!
Description: The Rutgers University Baseball Team welcomes NJ rival Seton Hall to Bainton Field. Come support your Scarlet Knights as they play their second game in the series against the Pirates.  The first pitch is at 1:00 PM.  For more information on Rutgers Baseball, please visit scarletknights.com.
Group: Rutgers Division of Intercollegiate Athletics - Baseball

Title: (12 p.m.) RU Field Hockey FRENZY!
Description: Join the Rutgers Field Hockey team for their annual Alumni Game and FRENZY Tournament!   The Alumni game will begin at noon and we welcome everyone in attendance to stay for a post game barbecue. After the BBQ, our FRENZY Tournament, a modified field hockey tournament, will kickoff.  All are welcome to participate in this fundraising event for Rutgers Field Hockey for a fee of $10. Due to NCAA compliance regulations, high school aged participants, or prospective student-athletes, are not permitted to participate. Visit scarletknights.com for additional information, as times may change.
Group: Rutgers Division of Intercollegiate Athletics - Field Hockey
